long_definition: ܗܽܘ he; ܗܽܘ ܟܰܕ ܗܽܘ the same.

Many phrases with ܒܰܪ, ܒܰܪܬ, ܒܢ̈ܰܝ, ܒܢ̈ܳܬ expressing relationship, belonging; e.g.: ܒܰܪ ܐܶܓܳܪܳܐ lunatic; ܒܰܪ ܐܺܝܬܽܘܬܳܐ consubstantial; ܒܰܪ ܐܢܳܫܳܐ, ܒܰܪܢܳܫܳܐ person, human being; ܒܰܪ ܐܰܬܪܳܐ compatriot, indigenous; ܒܰܪ ܒܰܝܬܳܐ bond slave, born in the house; human being, kindred; ܒܰܪ ܒܶܣܬܪܳܐܺܝܬ backwards; ܒܰܪ ܒܶܣܬܪܳܝܳܐ reverse; ܒܰܪ ܓܰܒܳܐ adherent (of a party, sect); ܒܰܪ ܓܶܢܣܳܐ kindred; ܒܰܪ ܙܰܘܓܳܐ husband; close companion; ܒܰܪܬ ܙܰܘܓܳܐ wife; ܒܰܪ ܚܺܐܪ̈ܶܐ noble, freeborn; ܒܰܪ ܟܝܳܢܳܐ consubstantial, of the same nature; ܒܰܪ ܠܘܺܝܬܳܐ travelling companion; ܒܰܪ ܡܕܺܝܢ̱ܬܳܐ citizen; ܒܰܪ ܡܶܠܟܳܐ counselor; ܒܰܪ ܥܳܠܡܳܐ layman; ܒܰܪ ܥܶܢܝܳܢܳܐ familiar friend; ܒܰܪ ܦܶܚܡܳܐ similar, Kth. colleague; ܒܰܪ ܩܝܳܡܳܐ / ܒܰܪ̱ܬ ܩܝܳܡܳܐ someone who has taken ascetic vows; Kth. f. wife of a priest; ܒܰܪ ܫܡܳܐ having the same name, namesake; ܒܰܪ ܫܳܥܬܳܐ, ܒܰܪ ܫܳܥܬܶܗ immediately.
ܒܪܳܐ fut. ܢܶܒܪܶܐ, Ia to create
ܒܰܪܳܐ exterior; open country; ܠܒܰܪ outside, out, ܠܒܰܪ ܡܶܢ apart from.
ܐܶܠܳܐ fut. ܢܶܐܠܶܐ, Ia to mourn, lament.
ܐܶܠܳܐ if not, unless; except, but.
ܐܶܬܳܐ fut. ܢܺܐܬܶܐ, imp. ܬܳܐ (f. ܬܳܝ) Ia to come, arrive; IIIa ܐܰܝܬܺܝ to bring, introduce; IIIp.
ܐܳܬܳܐ (pl. ܐܳܬܘ̈ܳܬܳܐ) f. sign, token, miracle.

ܐܺܝܕܳܐ (pl. ܐܺܝ̈ܕܶܐ, ܐܺܝܕܰܝ̈ܳܐ) f. hand; handle, etc; ܝܰܕ edge, side; ܒܝܰܕ through, by means of, with the help of; -ܒܝܰܕ ܕ because; ܡܶܢ ܝܰܕ on account of; ܥܰܠ ܝܰܕ beside; ܒܺܐܝܕܳܐ ܒܺܐܝܕܳܐ little by little; partly.
ܐܰܒ݂ܳܐ father; spiritual father; (pl. ܐܰܒ̈ܳܗܶܐ) parents, forefathers; (pl. ܐܰܒ̈ܳܗܳܬܳܐ) spiritual fathers.
ܚܝܳܐ fut. ܢܺܐܚܶܐ & ܢܺܚܶܐ, imp. ܚܝܺܝ, Ia to live, be alive, revive; to be saved; IIIa to give life, keep alive, save alive, bring to life; to save; IIIp.
ܪܽܘܚܳܐ (pl. ܪ̈ܽܘܚܶܐ, ܪ̈ܽܘܚܳܬܳܐ) f. (usually m. in prose for Holy Spirit) spirit; wind; ܪܽܘܚܳܐ ܕܩܽܘܕܫܳܐ, ܪܽܘܚܳܐ ܩܰܕܺܝܫܳܐ Holy Spirit.
ܣܓܳܐ & ܣܓܺܝ fut. ܢܶܣܓܶܐ, Ia to abound; to increase; IIa to multiply, increase (+ object); to do often; to sing a sughitho; Gram. to form a plural; IIIa to increase, to multiply; to do much.
ܛܶܒܳܐ news, tidings, report, fame; rumor; Gram. attribute.
ܛܳܒܳܐ good, excellent; precious (of stone); cultivated (of plant).

ܫܽܘܒܳܚܳܐ act of praise; section of the Psalter.

long_definition: ܫܽܘܒܚܳܐ praise, glory; splendor; opinion, tenet.

ܩܪܳܐ 1 fut. ܢܶܩܪܶܐ, Ia to call, summon, invite, invoke; Kth. to read; Ip.
ܩܠܳܐ fut. ܢܶܩܠܶܐ, Ia to fry, to toast; to kill; Ip to perish; to be scorned; IIa to fry; to excite; to scorn; IIp to be burnt up; to be displeased; to be inflamed; IIIa to fry; to provoke, vex. B - K
ܩܳܠܳܐ voice, sound; expression; hymn; tune; ܒܰܪܬ ܩܳܠܳܐ expression, quotation, Gram. word.

ܚܰܫܳܐ suffering, pain; sorrow, sadness; passion, affection; the Passion.

ܪܡܳܐ fut. ܢܶܪܡܶܐ, Ia to put, place; Ip to be lying down; to be thrown; to submit; to be occupied with; IIa to calumniate; IIp to be deceived; to agree; IIIa to throw, cast, put; to impose, to set upon; + ܐܺܝܕܳܐ to sign; IIIp to be cast out; to be laid aside; to be stored up; to be exposed (of children).
ܬܰܡܶܢ IIa to divide into eight.
